35 SECTION 5. ORS 90.302 is amended to read:
36 90.302. (1) A landlord may not charge a fee at the beginning of the tenancy for an anticipated
37 landlord expense and may not require the payment of any fee except as provided in this section.
38 A fee must be described in a written rental agreement.
39 (2) A landlord may charge a tenant a fee for each occurrence of the following:
40 (a) A late rent payment, pursuant to ORS 90.260.
41 (b) A dishonored check, pursuant to ORS 30.701 (5). The amount of the fee may not exceed the
42 amount described in ORS 30.701 (5) plus any amount that a bank has charged the landlord for pro-
43 cessing the dishonored check.
44 (c) Removal or tampering with a properly functioning smoke alarm, smoke detector or carbon
45 monoxide alarm, as provided in ORS 90.325 (2). The landlord may charge a fee of up to $250 unless
