11 vice, provided that the landlord also offers the tenant at least one alternative means of access,
12 including] and of unlocking or otherwise accessing all common areas or common facilities of
13 the premises to which the tenant has access, such as an access code or a fob, key card or other
14 tangible key which must include at least one means other than a tenant portal; or
15 (n) For a dwelling unit in a building where building permits for its construction were issued on
16 or after April 1, 2024, adequate cooling facilities that:
17 (A) Provide cooling in at least one room of the dwelling unit, not including a bathroom;
18 (B) Conform to applicable law at the time of installation and are maintained in good working
19 order; and
20 (C) May include central air conditioning, an air-source or ground-source heat pump or a portable
21 air conditioning device that is provided by the landlord.
22 (2) The landlord and tenant may agree in writing that the tenant is to perform specified repairs,
23 maintenance tasks and minor remodeling only if:
24 (a) The agreement of the parties is entered into in good faith and not for the purpose of evading
25 the obligations of the landlord;
26 (b) The agreement does not diminish the obligations of the landlord to other tenants in the
27 premises; and
28 (c) The terms and conditions of the agreement are clearly and fairly disclosed and adequate
29 consideration for the agreement is specifically stated.
30 (3) Any provisions of this section that reasonably apply only to a structure that is used as a
31 home, residence or sleeping place do not apply to a manufactured dwelling, recreational vehicle or
32 floating home where the tenant owns the manufactured dwelling, recreational vehicle or floating
33 home, rents the space and, in the case of a dwelling or home, the space is not in a facility. Manu-
34 factured dwelling or floating home tenancies in which the tenant owns the dwelling or home and
35 rents space in a facility are governed by ORS 90.730 and not by this section.
36 SECTION 7. (1) Sections 2 and 3 of this 2026 Act and the amendments to ORS 90.302 and
37 90.320 by sections 5 and 6 of this 2026 Act apply to rental agreements entered into before,
38 on or after the effective date of this 2026 Act.
39 (2) Section 2 of this 2026 Act applies to applications for a rental agreement screened on
40 or after the effective date of this 2026 Act.
41 SECTION 8. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
42 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
